      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": ".claude/skills/graphify/references/extraction-spec.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "A discrete rubric (1.0 EXTRACTED; 0.95/0.85/0.75/0.65/0.55 for INFERRED; 0.1-0.3 AMBIGUOUS) exists because models follow discrete rubrics better than continuous ranges - the bimodal distribution observed in production (over 50% at 0.5, over 40% at 0.85+) showed free-form guidance collapsing to a binary."
    },
    {
